cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM

The paper deals with the problem of long-term tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. The paper discusses the mathematical perspective of the problem and proposes a solution to reduce model decay. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the effect of various sources of tracking error on model decay, which involves machine learning techniques. Hence, it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper proposes a tracker that is evaluated on long-term and short-term tracking benchmarks, which involves robotics and multimedia. Therefore, it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
